  "response": "The Tagalog word \u201ckinikilig\u201d describes a feeling of excitement or giddiness, often associated with romantic feelings or infatuation. There isn't a direct English equivalent, but words or phrases like \"tingling,\" \"fluttering,\" or \"thrilled\" can capture similar emotions, often used in a romantic context. Sometimes, people also use \"swoon\" or say they feel \"giddy\" when referring to that feeling.",
